1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,420
<i>I'm confident we will win.</i>

2
00:00:03,503 --> 00:00:06,172
<i>You are fighting for</i>
<i>women who were abused.</i>

3
00:00:06,256 --> 00:00:08,591
<i>Do you know what you are giving them?</i>

4
00:00:08,675 --> 00:00:09,634
<i>Hope.</i>

5
00:00:11,678 --> 00:00:15,890
<i>Edward, the delivery of donations</i>
<i>for healing mass at Santa Fe,</i>

6
00:00:15,974 --> 00:00:17,308
<i>we'll take care of them.</i>

7
00:00:17,392 --> 00:00:18,852
<i>I can still manage.</i>

8
00:00:18,935 --> 00:00:20,729
<i>Really, this is my vow.</i>

9
00:00:20,812 --> 00:00:23,273
<i>Shouldn't we still continue our vows</i>

10
00:00:23,356 --> 00:00:24,774
<i>even when faced with hardship?</i>

11
00:00:24,858 --> 00:00:28,903
<i>Before, I thought healing</i>
<i>meant forgetting the past.</i>

12
00:00:28,987 --> 00:00:31,156
<i>But now I know I have to face it.</i>

13
00:00:31,573 --> 00:00:33,241
<i>You've come a long way,</i>

14
00:00:33,324 --> 00:00:35,994
<i>I heard you and Papa arguing.</i>

15
00:00:36,077 --> 00:00:39,789
<i>I know you're not happy here.</i>

16
00:00:39,873 --> 00:00:41,791
<i>Ever since Edong showed up,</i>

17
00:00:41,875 --> 00:00:43,585
<i>everything has changed.</i>

18
00:00:43,668 --> 00:00:45,795
<i>I love you and your dad so much.</i>

19
00:00:45,879 --> 00:00:47,589
<i>You are my life.</i>

20
00:00:48,631 --> 00:00:49,674
<i>There…</i>

21
00:00:50,175 --> 00:00:51,092
<i>There…</i>

22
00:00:56,681 --> 00:00:59,851
[girl singing]
♪<i> I am not afraid of the dark </i>♪

23
00:00:59,934 --> 00:01:02,145
♪ <i>Mark my word, my lazy brother </i>♪

24
00:01:02,228 --> 00:01:08,485
♪<i> I will get back at you one day! </i>♪

25
00:01:08,568 --> 00:01:13,490
[theme music playing]

26
00:02:15,468 --> 00:02:18,680
[suspenseful music playing]

27
00:02:23,476 --> 00:02:25,186
[gate creaks]

28
00:02:26,104 --> 00:02:27,063
There she is.

29
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:28,523
That's Kyle's mother.

30
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:38,491
[engine roars]

31
00:02:40,869 --> 00:02:41,870
[gate creaks]

32
00:02:41,953 --> 00:02:46,666
[suspenseful music continues]

33
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:49,711
[motorcycle humming]

34
00:02:49,794 --> 00:02:55,049
[suspenseful music continues]

35
00:03:02,599 --> 00:03:04,183
- [crickets chirping]
- [music fades]

36
00:03:13,234 --> 00:03:14,611
Chloe's asleep already.

37
00:03:23,745 --> 00:03:25,830
Why didn't you tell her the truth?

38
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:32,295
[pensive music playing]

39
00:03:34,797 --> 00:03:38,718
Yes, you lied about the watch.

40
00:03:39,677 --> 00:03:41,804
But our daughter is smart.

41
00:03:42,347 --> 00:03:43,681
Just like you.

42
00:03:44,807 --> 00:03:47,560
I'm sure she'll
understand why you did that.

43
00:03:49,020 --> 00:03:51,773
She doesn't think like kids her age.

44
00:03:52,607 --> 00:03:58,863
Chloe understands
that life isn’t just black and white.

45
00:03:59,989 --> 00:04:03,326
[pensive music continues]

46
00:04:03,409 --> 00:04:04,535
[sighs softly]

47
00:04:04,619 --> 00:04:06,204
I know that.

48
00:04:08,414 --> 00:04:10,541
But I'm still scared.

49
00:04:13,378 --> 00:04:15,338
I said it before, didn't I?

50
00:04:17,090 --> 00:04:19,092
I’m brave in many things.

51
00:04:21,344 --> 00:04:23,763
But when it comes to our daughter…

52
00:04:25,932 --> 00:04:27,517
But wouldn't it be better,

53
00:04:28,309 --> 00:04:30,061
if the truth came from you?

54
00:04:31,271 --> 00:04:33,064
Instead of finding out from someone else.

55
00:04:34,274 --> 00:04:39,654
[pensive music continues]

56
00:04:42,865 --> 00:04:44,033
You're right.

57
00:04:46,327 --> 00:04:48,037
I know you're right.

58
00:04:51,666 --> 00:04:52,875
Love…

59
00:04:54,252 --> 00:04:57,422
Don't worry. I will help you.

60
00:04:58,172 --> 00:05:00,967
I will be there when you talk to Chloe.

61
00:05:01,884 --> 00:05:04,929
Just tell me when you're ready.

62
00:05:05,555 --> 00:05:11,227
[pensive music continues]

63
00:05:12,186 --> 00:05:14,772
[breathes shakily]

64
00:05:18,693 --> 00:05:20,486
- [crickets chirping]
- [music fades]

65
00:05:30,246 --> 00:05:31,080
[car door opens]

66
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:34,751
[door closes]

67
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:39,380
[Erica] From what I know,
this is the house of Kyle's relative.

68
00:05:40,506 --> 00:05:42,759
I learned about this
house when we were kids.

69
00:05:43,634 --> 00:05:45,136
They say the house is haunted.

70
00:05:45,219 --> 00:05:48,514
[dramatic music playing]

71
00:05:48,598 --> 00:05:51,559
[motorcycle approaching]

72
00:05:54,353 --> 00:05:55,396
[engine shuts off]

73
00:05:55,480 --> 00:06:00,485
[dramatic music continues]

74
00:06:16,501 --> 00:06:18,086
[Marco] They're both inside.

75
00:06:18,669 --> 00:06:20,171
Do you think Kyle is there too?

76
00:06:20,755 --> 00:06:21,881
Possibly.

77
00:06:22,381 --> 00:06:25,093
Why else would
they come here at this hour?

78
00:06:25,176 --> 00:06:28,012
It's like they don't
want anyone to see them.

79
00:06:28,096 --> 00:06:32,683
[dramatic music continues]

80
00:06:47,615 --> 00:06:52,578
[dramatic music crescendos]

81
00:06:52,662 --> 00:06:53,788
[woman] Katkat!

82
00:06:54,580 --> 00:06:58,209
Katkat! I need you to
buy oil from the store. We're out already.

83
00:06:58,292 --> 00:07:00,128
Me again, Ma?

84
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:01,379
Why don't you ask him?

85
00:07:01,462 --> 00:07:03,548
He's just playing on his phone!

86
00:07:03,631 --> 00:07:06,134
Because I told you to do it,
so do as I say!

87
00:07:06,217 --> 00:07:07,301
Go on!

88
00:07:07,385 --> 00:07:10,263
I need to cook dinner
before your father gets home.

89
00:07:10,346 --> 00:07:12,265
Go on! Get!

90
00:07:12,348 --> 00:07:15,518
Ma, I don't want
to go to the store at night!

91
00:07:15,601 --> 00:07:18,771
Look how dark it is! It's so scary!

92
00:07:18,855 --> 00:07:21,357
You're too big
to still be afraid of the dark!

93
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:22,859
Come on, hurry up!

94
00:07:22,942 --> 00:07:26,821
- [crickets chirping]
- [electricity zapping]

95
00:07:40,543 --> 00:07:41,711
[gate handle clanking]

96
00:07:46,299 --> 00:07:47,633
What do you want?

97
00:07:48,843 --> 00:07:49,760
Good evening.

98
00:07:49,844 --> 00:07:51,554
My name is Atty. Erica Melendez,

99
00:07:51,637 --> 00:07:53,014
and this is Lucas Santiago.

100
00:07:53,097 --> 00:07:54,932
[Myrna] I know who you people are.

101
00:07:55,391 --> 00:07:56,851
What I want to know is,

102
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:58,811
why are you here?

103
00:07:58,895 --> 00:08:01,439
We just wanted to talk to you about Kyle.

104
00:08:01,772 --> 00:08:03,065
Stop this!

105
00:08:03,608 --> 00:08:05,568
Tell that to your friends, too!

106
00:08:06,152 --> 00:08:08,070
This is harassment.

107
00:08:08,571 --> 00:08:10,072
Next time you come back here,

108
00:08:10,156 --> 00:08:11,866
I'm going to call the police!

109
00:08:13,618 --> 00:08:17,330
[tense music playing]

110
00:08:17,413 --> 00:08:18,956
Kyle's not in the U.S., is he?

111
00:08:20,291 --> 00:08:21,417
He's here.

112
00:08:22,293 --> 00:08:23,377
Inside.

113
00:08:29,175 --> 00:08:34,430
[suspenseful music playing]

114
00:08:42,813 --> 00:08:43,898
[heavy thud]

115
00:08:43,981 --> 00:08:49,403
[suspenseful music continues]

116
00:09:08,589 --> 00:09:11,842
[electricity zapping]

117
00:09:11,926 --> 00:09:17,014
[suspenseful music continues]

118
00:09:33,114 --> 00:09:38,536
[suspenseful music continues]

119
00:09:43,457 --> 00:09:44,834
He's not here!

120
00:09:45,710 --> 00:09:47,336
So, what are you doing here?

121
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:50,006
We just saw your friend follow you.

122
00:09:50,965 --> 00:09:52,383
Who did you come to see?

123
00:09:53,134 --> 00:09:56,345
If people find out we came here,

124
00:09:56,429 --> 00:09:59,390
I'm really going to file
a harassment complaint against you!

125
00:10:00,224 --> 00:10:01,767
Just what are you hiding?

126
00:10:12,945 --> 00:10:18,784
[suspenseful music intensifies]

127
00:10:18,868 --> 00:10:19,952
[gunshot]

128
00:10:20,036 --> 00:10:23,080
[thrilling music playing]

129
00:10:23,164 --> 00:10:24,123
Erica!

130
00:10:24,206 --> 00:10:25,625
[panicked breaths]

131
00:10:29,670 --> 00:10:30,796
[Travis] Son of a--

132
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:32,882
- Marco!
- What are you two doing here?

133
00:10:36,552 --> 00:10:39,305
- Marco!
- [man] Don't fucking look at me.

134
00:10:39,388 --> 00:10:41,390
[thrilling music fades]

135
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:47,813
[ominous music playing]

136
00:10:50,608 --> 00:10:54,320
[dramatic music stings]

137
00:10:58,449 --> 00:10:59,617
Kyle?

138
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:01,535
Don't fucking look at me!

139
00:11:01,619 --> 00:11:03,746
[music becomes tense]

140
00:11:03,829 --> 00:11:05,956
I said, don't fucking look at me!

141
00:11:06,791 --> 00:11:07,958
Fucking bitch!

142
00:11:10,169 --> 00:11:11,170
Don't look at me!

143
00:11:11,253 --> 00:11:15,633
[tense music continues]

144
00:11:22,473 --> 00:11:23,516
[Travis] Kyle…

145
00:11:26,018 --> 00:11:27,686
Don't fucking look at me!

146
00:11:30,606 --> 00:11:35,319
[tense music intensifies]

147
00:11:35,403 --> 00:11:39,657
[suspenseful music playing]

148
00:11:39,740 --> 00:11:40,741
[Kyle grunts]

149
00:11:40,825 --> 00:11:41,992
- [Travis] Kyle!
- [gun clatters]

150
00:11:42,076 --> 00:11:46,330
[Kyle breathing heavily]

151
00:11:46,414 --> 00:11:47,248
[Myrna] Son!

152
00:11:48,416 --> 00:11:49,417
Are you okay?

153
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:51,752
[music fades]

154
00:11:53,504 --> 00:11:55,548
Why can't you just leave us alone?

155
00:11:55,631 --> 00:11:57,174
I already told you!

156
00:11:57,258 --> 00:12:00,219
My son had nothing
to do with your friend's death!

157
00:12:00,302 --> 00:12:01,345
[Travis] Damn you!

158
00:12:01,429 --> 00:12:03,305
It's been so long! Just move on!

159
00:12:03,389 --> 00:12:06,100
Who you're fighting for is
nothing but a skeleton now!

160
00:12:06,183 --> 00:12:08,477
What? Were you hoping
Louisa would come back from the dead?

161
00:12:08,561 --> 00:12:09,520
Louisa?

162
00:12:11,522 --> 00:12:13,065
Why are you bringing up that bitch?

163
00:12:14,233 --> 00:12:15,067
Huh?

164
00:12:15,151 --> 00:12:17,820
After all this time…
You still disrespect her, Kyle?

165
00:12:18,904 --> 00:12:22,491
We found out you were
here on the night she was killed.

166
00:12:23,909 --> 00:12:24,994
Was it you?

167
00:12:26,287 --> 00:12:27,788
Did you kill her?

168
00:12:27,872 --> 00:12:28,831
What?

169
00:12:29,290 --> 00:12:31,083
You had threatened us in the past.

170
00:12:31,542 --> 00:12:33,544
<i>Think you got one over me?</i>

171
00:12:33,627 --> 00:12:34,712
<i>Watch your backs.</i>

172
00:12:34,795 --> 00:12:36,213
"I'll get back at you."

173
00:12:36,297 --> 00:12:37,798
<i>I'll get back at you.</i>

174
00:12:37,882 --> 00:12:39,216
[dramatic music playing]

175
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:40,634
That's what you said.

176
00:12:41,302 --> 00:12:44,763
Did you go through
with your threat to hurt us?

177
00:12:45,848 --> 00:12:47,516
Did you kill Louisa?

178
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:48,934
What the hell are you talking about?

179
00:12:49,018 --> 00:12:50,895
I was already in the States by the time.

180
00:12:50,978 --> 00:12:54,398
What makes you think I was
still thinking of that fucking bitch?

181
00:12:54,899 --> 00:12:56,484
I don't give a damn about her.

182
00:12:56,567 --> 00:12:58,903
Just like I don't give
a fuck about you guys. Got it?

183
00:12:58,986 --> 00:13:00,196
If that's true,

184
00:13:01,447 --> 00:13:02,865
where were you that night?

185
00:13:03,365 --> 00:13:04,700
What were you doing?

186
00:13:07,703 --> 00:13:09,163
You don't need to reply.

187
00:13:10,623 --> 00:13:12,833
[Lucas] Why? Is he guilty?

188
00:13:13,417 --> 00:13:15,169
Because he doesn't need to.

189
00:13:18,172 --> 00:13:19,840
You bastards. Just go!

190
00:13:19,924 --> 00:13:21,217
Come on, get out of here!

191
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:24,762
We're not leaving until
we get a proper answer!

192
00:13:24,845 --> 00:13:25,971
Just call the police.

193
00:13:26,055 --> 00:13:27,473
- Dial them now.
- [Erica] Seriously?

194
00:13:27,556 --> 00:13:28,933
Do you really want that?

195
00:13:30,142 --> 00:13:32,853
So you want everyone
to know that you're hiding here, Kyle?

196
00:13:32,937 --> 00:13:36,732
[tense music playing]

197
00:13:36,815 --> 00:13:38,192
It all makes sense now.

198
00:13:38,275 --> 00:13:41,195
Why you didn't tell anyone in the U.S.
about him coming back here.

199
00:13:41,987 --> 00:13:43,739
What are you running away from, Kyle?

200
00:13:44,782 --> 00:13:45,866
Huh?

201
00:13:46,951 --> 00:13:48,244
Those burn scars…

202
00:13:48,827 --> 00:13:50,329
They look fresh.

203
00:13:51,539 --> 00:13:52,748
Just a few months old.

204
00:13:54,250 --> 00:13:55,459
So, what exactly happened?

205
00:13:56,168 --> 00:13:58,254
Did you harass another woman?

206
00:13:59,088 --> 00:14:02,341
Then you realized you messed up

207
00:14:03,008 --> 00:14:04,385
because she fought back?

208
00:14:05,386 --> 00:14:07,805
- Is that it?
- Blah, blah, blah, blah. Shut up.

209
00:14:07,888 --> 00:14:10,849
Shut the fuck up, you fucking bitch!

210
00:14:11,517 --> 00:14:13,519
Shut up! Shut up!

211
00:14:13,602 --> 00:14:15,396
So, I was right.

212
00:14:17,064 --> 00:14:17,940
Huh?

213
00:14:18,023 --> 00:14:22,736
[tense music continues]

214
00:14:22,820 --> 00:14:26,532
How many more
women are you going to abuse?!

215
00:14:29,660 --> 00:14:31,370
[music fades]

216
00:14:31,453 --> 00:14:32,329
It's Michelle!

217
00:14:32,413 --> 00:14:34,164
[foreboding music playing]

218
00:14:34,248 --> 00:14:36,375
<i>You freaking bitch!</i>

219
00:14:36,792 --> 00:14:37,877
<i>Thank you!</i>

220
00:14:39,545 --> 00:14:41,380
I was with Michelle.

221
00:14:42,715 --> 00:14:44,174
The night of Louisa's murder,

222
00:14:44,633 --> 00:14:45,968
I just bumped into her.

223
00:14:46,927 --> 00:14:50,180
She was mad at Romeo
because he kissed Louisa.

224
00:14:51,265 --> 00:14:54,268
Michelle wanted to get back at him,
so we hooked up.

225
00:14:54,351 --> 00:14:55,644
Don't lie to me.

226
00:14:55,728 --> 00:14:57,521
Fucking ask her!

227
00:14:57,897 --> 00:14:59,273
Fucking ask her.

228
00:15:01,108 --> 00:15:02,151
Go.

229
00:15:03,736 --> 00:15:08,949
[ominous music playing]

230
00:15:09,491 --> 00:15:11,452
My son has answered your questions.

231
00:15:11,535 --> 00:15:12,995
Now, leave!

232
00:15:15,831 --> 00:15:21,921
[ominous music continues]

233
00:15:26,008 --> 00:15:28,135
I'm glad that fucking bitch was murdered.

234
00:15:28,218 --> 00:15:31,889
[music turns tense]

235
00:15:35,684 --> 00:15:36,769
Erica…

236
00:15:39,688 --> 00:15:41,649
No woman will ever come near you again.

237
00:15:43,233 --> 00:15:46,946
One look at you,
and even a ghost would run away.

238
00:15:48,405 --> 00:15:50,282
Because you're ugly inside and out.

239
00:15:51,367 --> 00:15:52,952
- [groans]
- [Kyle's mother] Son!

240
00:15:55,037 --> 00:15:56,246
[Myrna] Are you okay?

241
00:15:57,539 --> 00:16:01,251
[pained screams]

242
00:16:06,924 --> 00:16:12,096
- [unsettling music playing]
- [electricity zapping]

243
00:16:28,112 --> 00:16:34,785
[unsettling music continues]

244
00:16:37,579 --> 00:16:38,580
[knocks on door]

245
00:16:39,206 --> 00:16:40,290
Who is it?!

246
00:16:40,374 --> 00:16:42,501
Who's knocking at this hour?

247
00:16:43,168 --> 00:16:44,044
[huffs]

248
00:16:44,878 --> 00:16:45,921
What is it?!

249
00:16:46,463 --> 00:16:47,423
Uh…

250
00:16:47,923 --> 00:16:50,384
On the night of Louisa's murder,
were you with Kyle?

251
00:16:51,885 --> 00:16:52,803
W- What?

252
00:16:52,886 --> 00:16:53,971
That's what he told us.

253
00:16:56,140 --> 00:16:57,224
Is that true?

254
00:16:58,100 --> 00:16:59,476
- What did you--
- We had sex!

255
00:17:00,644 --> 00:17:01,603
Okay?

256
00:17:02,938 --> 00:17:04,023
Why are you asking me this?

257
00:17:04,106 --> 00:17:05,107
What time?

258
00:17:05,190 --> 00:17:06,859
And until what time were you together?

259
00:17:08,318 --> 00:17:10,446
After I beat up Louisa.

260
00:17:10,529 --> 00:17:12,239
And after I beat Romeo up, too.

261
00:17:13,824 --> 00:17:17,745
I couldn't believe Romeo
would kiss someone like Louisa.

262
00:17:18,787 --> 00:17:20,414
So I walked out on him.

263
00:17:21,290 --> 00:17:23,417
And then I saw Kyle.

264
00:17:23,959 --> 00:17:25,294
We bumped into each other.

265
00:17:25,878 --> 00:17:26,962
So…

266
00:17:28,213 --> 00:17:31,175
We had sex until the sun came up.

267
00:17:35,137 --> 00:17:36,305
So?

268
00:17:36,388 --> 00:17:37,890
Don't you believe me?

269
00:17:38,974 --> 00:17:41,518
I knew this day would come.

270
00:17:41,602 --> 00:17:44,313
I knew people won't
believe that I hooked up with Kyle.

271
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:46,315
Just a sec. I'll look for it.

272
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:49,359
Here you go.

273
00:17:50,235 --> 00:17:51,320
Look at it!

274
00:17:51,403 --> 00:17:55,282
[dramatic music playing]

275
00:17:55,365 --> 00:17:56,325
Fuck!

276
00:17:56,742 --> 00:17:57,910
Now, get off my back!

277
00:17:58,327 --> 00:18:00,120
When we talked to you about Louisa,

278
00:18:00,204 --> 00:18:01,955
why didn't you tell us about Kyle?

279
00:18:02,039 --> 00:18:04,500
Oh, is that my fault?

280
00:18:04,583 --> 00:18:06,710
You didn't ask me about Kyle.

281
00:18:06,794 --> 00:18:09,213
You just asked me about Louisa, remember?

282
00:18:11,298 --> 00:18:13,092
Besides, he told me

283
00:18:13,175 --> 00:18:15,761
to not tell anyone
that he's back in Amurao.

284
00:18:15,844 --> 00:18:17,679
So, I kept my mouth shut.

285
00:18:17,763 --> 00:18:19,139
[music fades]

286
00:18:19,223 --> 00:18:22,810
Also, after I got back at Romeo…

287
00:18:24,103 --> 00:18:25,479
him and I made up.

288
00:18:28,315 --> 00:18:29,399
But…

289
00:18:30,067 --> 00:18:31,318
But that's all in the past now.

290
00:18:31,819 --> 00:18:34,238
Um… I'm single.

291
00:18:34,822 --> 00:18:36,031
Single…

292
00:18:36,990 --> 00:18:38,534
- [Erica scoffs]
- [giggles]

293
00:18:42,621 --> 00:18:43,664
Bye.

294
00:18:52,965 --> 00:18:54,049
[Alice sighs sharply]

295
00:18:57,886 --> 00:18:59,054
What are you doing?

296
00:18:59,888 --> 00:19:01,431
I'm preparing your stuff.

297
00:19:02,891 --> 00:19:04,935
The moment the doctor gives the go signal,

298
00:19:05,018 --> 00:19:07,729
you and Seth are flying out of here, okay?

299
00:19:10,190 --> 00:19:11,191
Alice… Alice.

300
00:19:12,067 --> 00:19:13,068
What?

301
00:19:13,152 --> 00:19:15,946
I already told you,
I don't want to leave you here.

302
00:19:17,531 --> 00:19:19,783
Scott, please.

303
00:19:20,784 --> 00:19:22,578
You have to take Seth away from here.

304
00:19:25,205 --> 00:19:26,748
But who will protect you?

305
00:19:28,876 --> 00:19:29,751
[scoffs]

306
00:19:31,044 --> 00:19:32,796
[huffs] We have the police.

307
00:19:34,214 --> 00:19:35,841
We have security.

308
00:19:37,092 --> 00:19:38,510
And I promise…

309
00:19:39,636 --> 00:19:41,054
I'm gonna be careful.

310
00:19:42,181 --> 00:19:44,975
Just… You just have
to take Seth away from here, Scott.

311
00:19:45,058 --> 00:19:47,644
It's… It's the only way
I'm gonna be able to breathe.

312
00:19:50,397 --> 00:19:54,151
Look, I… I know I've messed
up a lot of things in our marriage.

313
00:19:55,944 --> 00:19:57,362
I know I've been…

314
00:19:57,446 --> 00:19:58,614
scared.

315
00:19:59,781 --> 00:20:03,035
But please, I'm asking
you to trust me this time, Scott.

316
00:20:03,660 --> 00:20:04,995
Just trust me.

317
00:20:06,205 --> 00:20:07,456
I can do this.

318
00:20:08,207 --> 00:20:12,211
[pensive music playing]

319
00:20:14,671 --> 00:20:17,216
Well, you weren't
scared the first time we met.

320
00:20:18,425 --> 00:20:19,468
Remember?

321
00:20:22,221 --> 00:20:23,764
[Scott] I was the one who was scared.

322
00:20:25,140 --> 00:20:26,975
And you were the one protecting me.

323
00:20:27,059 --> 00:20:29,853
[pensive music continues]

324
00:20:29,937 --> 00:20:31,605
I trust you, Alice.

325
00:20:33,565 --> 00:20:36,526
[breathes deeply]

326
00:20:37,653 --> 00:20:38,737
Alright.

327
00:20:39,363 --> 00:20:40,447
I'll take Seth home.

328
00:20:41,615 --> 00:20:43,033
But as soon as I can,

329
00:20:43,742 --> 00:20:45,535
I will come back for you.

330
00:20:49,373 --> 00:20:51,124
Just promise me that…

331
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:54,294
you'll come back home to me. Okay?

332
00:20:55,212 --> 00:21:00,634
[pensive music continues]

333
00:21:00,717 --> 00:21:01,969
I promise.

334
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:18,819
[music fades]

335
00:21:18,902 --> 00:21:25,325
[unsettling music playing]

336
00:21:25,409 --> 00:21:30,747
♪ <i>I'm not scared of the dark</i>
<i>Even though my brother's lazy</i> ♪

337
00:21:30,831 --> 00:21:36,753
♪<i> Someday, I'll get back at him </i>♪

338
00:21:36,837 --> 00:21:38,213
[leaves crunch]

339
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:41,591
Who's there?

340
00:21:42,134 --> 00:21:43,093
Big brother?

341
00:21:44,261 --> 00:21:45,304
Brother?

342
00:21:45,387 --> 00:21:48,473
[electricity zapping]

343
00:21:48,557 --> 00:21:53,312
♪<i> I'm not scared of the dark</i>
<i>Even though my brother's lazy </i>♪

344
00:21:53,395 --> 00:21:56,064
♪<i> Someday… </i>♪

345
00:21:56,148 --> 00:21:58,191
[leaves crunching]

346
00:22:03,280 --> 00:22:09,786
[unsettling music continues]

347
00:22:15,125 --> 00:22:16,460
[man] Why are you crying?

348
00:22:16,918 --> 00:22:20,172
I thought someone was following me.

349
00:22:20,630 --> 00:22:21,923
[man] Don't be scared.

350
00:22:22,966 --> 00:22:24,426
There's no one behind you.

351
00:22:27,721 --> 00:22:29,848
- [relieved sigh]
- [music fades]

352
00:22:30,390 --> 00:22:32,142
- [man grunts]
- [muffled screaming]

353
00:22:32,225 --> 00:22:37,147
[sinister music playing]

354
00:22:37,731 --> 00:22:41,109
[muffled screams]

355
00:22:43,987 --> 00:22:47,407
<i>And you, you've been there for a while,</i>

356
00:22:47,491 --> 00:22:50,535
<i>convincing others</i>
<i>that you're normal and safe.</i>

357
00:22:50,619 --> 00:22:53,330
<i>But we both know no one's safe from you.</i>

358
00:22:53,413 --> 00:22:54,664
<i>He's out of his mind!</i>

359
00:22:54,748 --> 00:22:56,208
<i>The cops are still looking for Edong.</i>

360
00:22:56,291 --> 00:22:57,918
<i>We can still solve Louisa's case.</i>

361
00:22:58,001 --> 00:22:59,711
<i>Your life is at risk here.</i>

362
00:22:59,795 --> 00:23:02,172
<i>If something bad happens to you,</i>
<i>I wouldn't be able to take it.</i>

363
00:23:02,255 --> 00:23:04,299
<i>You can't stop me.</i>

364
00:23:04,382 --> 00:23:07,094
<i>I'd stand on top of your dead body</i>

365
00:23:07,177 --> 00:23:09,012
<i>if that's what it takes to get to them.</i>

366
00:23:09,096 --> 00:23:11,264
[chuckles]
